 "target_response": {
  "text": "Suppressed means your HRV is running below your own normal range, not that something is wrong in absolute terms. Today you're at 66 ms against a 30-day average of 73 ms, and single days this far under baseline usually reflect accumulated training or short sleep — last night was 6.1 hours, under your weekly 7-hour average, after a 90-minute row. It matters as a caution light, not an alarm: your recovery still reads 64% and resting heart rate at 51 bpm is fine. Care about it by responding, not worrying — keep today easy-to-moderate and bank an earlier night, then see if the trend lifts.",
